headlines.description: — Jabari Smith Jr. had 21 points and 11 rebounds, Fred VanVleet added 20 points and the Houston Rockets beat the Charlotte Hornets 114-101 on Monday night for their third straight win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jabari Smith Jr. scores 21 as Rockets run away from Hornets 114-101 for third straight victory

headlines.description: — Darius Garland scored 23 points and the NBA-best Cleveland Cavaliers beat the Utah Jazz 124-113 on Monday night for their 17th victory in 18 home games.
headlines.shortLinkText: Darius Garland scores 23 and NBA-best Cavaliers beat Jazz 124-113 for 17th home win in 18 games

headlines.description: — Tristan da Silva scored 18 points and made a critical 3-pointer with 9.9 seconds left, and the Orlando Magic rallied from a 15-point halftime deficit Monday night for a 108-104 victory over the Boston Celtics, who were missing Jayson Tatum because...
headlines.shortLinkText: Da Silva's late 3 preserves Magic's 108-104 comeback win over Tatum-less Celtics

headlines.description: — Tyrese Maxey scored 32 points and made two crucial plays in the final minute, and the Philadelphia 76ers rallied after <a...
headlines.shortLinkText: Maxey rallies the 76ers to a 111-106 victory over the Spurs after Embiid is ejected

headlines.description: — Garrison Mathews made a career-best seven 3-pointers and scored a season-high 25 points off the bench as the Atlanta Hawks knocked off the Minnesota Timberwolves 117-104 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mathews and Young lead the Hawks past the Timberwolves 117-104

headlines.description: — Bam Adebayo scored 17 of his 23 points in the second half and the Miami Heat snapped a three-game skid with a 110-95 win over the Brooklyn Nets on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Adebayo scores 23 points as Heat snap 3-game skid with 110-95 win over Nets

events.name: Toronto Raptors at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Karl-Anthony Towns had 31 points, 10 rebounds and seven assists, OG Anunoby also scored 31 points and shot 13 for 15 from the field, and the New York Knicks beat the Toronto Raptors 139-125 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Towns and Anunoby each score 31 points to lead the Knicks past the Raptors, 139-125

headlines.description: — Khris Middleton and Brook Lopez each scored 21 points, Bobby Portis added 19 points and 13 rebounds, and the Milwaukee Bucks beat the Chicago Bulls 112-91 on Monday without Giannis Antetokounmpo and Damian Lillard.
headlines.shortLinkText: Middleton and Lopez lead the way as Bucks pound Bulls 112-91 without Giannis, Lillard

headlines.description: — Norman Powell scored 29 points, including four in the final 25 seconds to lead the Los Angeles Clippers to a 114-110 victory over the Memphis Grizzlies on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Powell leads the Clippers to a 114-110 victory over the Grizzlies

events.name: Washington Wizards at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander scored 41 points and the Oklahoma City Thunder beat Washington 123-105 on Monday night, sending the NBA-worst Wizards to their 21st loss in 23 games and 12th straight on the road.
headlines.shortLinkText: Shai Gilgeous-Alexander scores 41 in Thunder's 123-105 win over Wizards

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Dallas Mavericks

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic returned from a two-game absence to score 27 points, Daniel Gafford added 23 off the bench and Kyrie Irving finished with 20 as the Dallas Mavericks beat the Portland Trail Blazers 132-108 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Luka Doncic returns to the lineup and scores 27 as the Mavericks beat the Trail Blazers 132-108

headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic scored 13 of his 32 points in a decisive third quarter, and the Denver Nuggets routed the scuffling Phoenix Suns 117-90 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jokic scores 32 points and the Nuggets rout the Suns 117-90

events.name: Indiana Pacers at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Myles Turner made a 3-pointer from the top of the arc with 16 seconds left and had 23 points and 10 rebounds, Pascal Siakam added 20 points and the Indiana Pacers beat the Golden State Warriors 111-105 on Monday night for their fifth straight win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Myles Turner hits late 3-pointer, scores 23 as Pacers beat Warriors 111-105

events.name: Detroit Pistons at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — Malik Beasley scored 21 points, Cade Cunningham had 20 points and 10 assists, and the Detroit Pistons held off the Los Angeles Lakers 117-114 Monday night to sweep the clubs' season series.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pistons overcome LeBron's triple-double, beat Lakers 117-114 to sweep their season series
